Class Vector2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • contents.Vector2D

  • public class Vector2D
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a Vector class for two-dimensional positions. An object's "Vector2D" is going to represent It's position. The 'D' in this class does not stand for "Double". It is just a way to say that this class is used for two-dimensional entities.

      • subtract

        public Vector2D subtract(Vector2D vec)
        Subtracts the points of "vec" from this vector. The 'x' values will subtract from one another and the 'y' values will do the same. Since you do not directly subtract two vectors, it just adds the negative vector of 'vec.'
        Parameters:
        vec - -- The vector that is to be subtracted from this one.
        Returns:
        Returns the updated vector.

      • negative

        public Vector2D negative()
        Returns this vector as a negative vector. For example... Vector2D vec1 = new Vector2D(3,5); System.out.println(vec1.toString()); ^ That will print out, "Vector2D: (3,5)" However, if you do this... System.out.println(vec1.negative().toString()); You will get the negative of the vector, and it will print out, "Vector2D: (-3,-5)"
        Returns:
        This vector, but as a negative.

      • UnitX
